    "description": "<span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3036070/extras/a9cc5792162673596a4b79c882950153.avif?t=1717921951\" width=616 height=100 /></span><br><strong>Flash Diving</strong> is a <u>claustrophobic short horror experience</u> where <strong>sound will be key</strong> to ensuring the success of your mission and your own survival, heavily inspired by games such as<strong> Iron Lung</strong> and <strong>Five Nights at Freddy's</strong>.<br><br><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3036070/extras/d50e0fccaedd0509224c806f88e1c2ef.poster.avif?t=1717921951\" width=616 height=340 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3036070/extras/d50e0fccaedd0509224c806f88e1c2ef.webm?t=1717921951\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3036070/extras/d50e0fccaedd0509224c806f88e1c2ef.mp4?t=1717921951\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span><br><br>Descend through a drill-made hole <u>in the middle of an ocean</u> in order to find the drill itself, or what remains of it.<br><br>Use the <strong>four old floodlights</strong> outside your small capsule to uncover what is hiding in your surroundings. But be careful, the technology is prmitive and <strong>it might take a while to charge the flash</strong>.<br><br><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3036070/extras/TEST1.gif?t=1717921951\" /></span><br><br>The game uses a <strong>minimal control scheme</strong>, similar to a walking simulator, where you can just walk and click.<br><br>The art style employs a <strong>pixelated look</strong> and low-poly models to reminisce about older games with lower resolutions, but where gameplay was profound and fun to play.<br><br><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3036070/extras/ccc8a795c0c03d0101a881d51eaab02a.avif?t=1717921951\" width=616 height=338 /></span><br><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3036070/extras/f138292dec7e89197cc89b62aa6f15a2.avif?t=1717921951\" width=616 height=100 /></span><br>As of today, there are no remaining natural resources on your planet, and the cold war that has been going on between nations has only made the situation worse. Your government, in a desperate attempt to gain an advantage over their enemies, sent a drill to the middle of the central ocean, since a geolocation analysis had found an anomaly in that place. Upon reaching the anomaly, connection with the drill was lost.<br><br>It is thought that one of the opposing nations might have found the operation and interacted with the expedition, so you are sent in a small capsule, controlled by a ship in the exterior, to reach the drill and ensure the connection to its database and the retrieval of the results.<br><br><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3036070/extras/a16727a736e1b51e7f46750863c5f607.avif?t=1717921951\" width=616 height=342 /></span>",
